Add VAT threshold dashboard widget (step 2/3)

- New `lib/use-vat-status.ts` hook: loads urssaf_profile + YTD income
  transactions filtered by calendar year, composes a VatStatus via
  the pure `lib/vat.ts` engine, and stays live through realtime
  subscriptions on both `transactions` and `urssaf_profile`.
- New `app/dashboard/vat-threshold-card.tsx` widget with four visual
  states (safe / warning / danger / exceeded) on a single morphing
  surface. Hidden when the user is already VAT-registered. Always
  visible regardless of the period dropdown — VAT thresholds are
  calendar-year based, not URSSAF-period based.
- New `app/dashboard/vat-explainer-dialog.tsx` modal with a
  personalized example (1 000 EUR HT vs 1 200 EUR TTC) and the user's
  actual seuil (41 250 EUR or 93 500 EUR HT).
- Integrated into the dashboard between SafeWithdrawCard and the
  cashflow chart so the cashflow context flows naturally into the
  VAT context.

No regression on the 101 existing Vitest cases; lint clean.
